        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="1337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.7146/3–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-28T18:00:00-05:00">March 28, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. B–3 report from Shanghai reed via controlled American source states Commies
                    Peiping suspect AmConGen of harboring Kmt “war <pb facs="1085" n="1075" xml:id="pg_1075"/> criminals”. Source of opinion report may indicate
                    possible pretext for increased restrictions on ConGen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
